cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and understanding in multi-party conversations. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on speaker interactions and role-sensitive embeddings could also place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of sequence prediction and the potential application in chatbots and conversational agents could make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
